    Instructions

    Lab 3: CPU Basics Part 1

    Please fill out the following quiz and note the following: 

    1) For questions that require writing RISC-V assembly, the instruction format is broken up between lines. For example: 

    add xs1, xs2, xs3 would be: 

    add xs1, 

    xs2, xs3

    2) For instructions that do not depend on register order, please order the registers in numerical order. For example: 

    add xs4, xs3, xs2 should be written as add x4, xs2, xs3.

    3) Some instructions may not fill in all the required blanks (such as jal). If this is the case, select the blank option from the drop down menu. 

    4) Some labels are given. For instance, 

    L1: 

    Refers to the line that comes after the instructions you are filling in.

    5) The solutions for every question that requires writing RISC V assembly will be shown after the question. You cannot go back to questions one you answer them.
